[00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.200]   This is a Kellblad post from September 5, 2006 titled "Galic Subtlety, Branding, Mark Logic,
[00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:10.480]   and Mark Logic." Respected online analytic processing, OLAP, Pundit, Englishman, and
[00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:15.360]   curmudgeon Nigel Pency, once wrote in a product review that, with "galic subtlety, business
[00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:20.880]   objects, the company" was two words while business objects, the product, was one. The observation,
[00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:24.800]   unnoticed by most people, was absolutely correct and I chuckled the other day when I saw this
[00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:29.600]   post by Bill Tripp, which reminded me of it. Bill is indeed correct when it comes to Mark Logic.
[00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:33.680]   Mark Logic, one word, refers to the product whose full name is Mark Logic Server,
[00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:38.000]   while Mark Logic, two words, refers to the company whose full name is Mark Logic Corporation.
[00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:41.520]   Why do we have this distinction? Do I view it as a best practice that I carried over from my
[00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:46.560]   prior job? Absolutely not. Somewhat amazingly, I managed to inherit the issue both times.
[00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:50.320]   While I won't review the business object's history, I will review the Mark Logic one.
[00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:54.880]   But first, some principles that I actually do consider best practices when it comes to naming
[00:00:54.880 --> 00:01:00.880]   B branding. Next, brands should be short, two to three syllables where possible, e.g. Google,
[00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:07.280]   Yahoo, PayPal. Next, brands should work in multiple languages. Often a Latin root helps e.g. Oracle.
[00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:12.160]   Care should be taken to avoid the Chevy Nova problem. Nova means "no-go" in Spanish,
[00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:16.000]   hardly an ideal name for a car. Next, brands should be pronounceable.
[00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.720]   People hate sounding stupid, so they dislike saying words they don't know how to pronounce.
[00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:25.520]   Why do you think Bullio Vineyards encourages people to call its wine BV? How many times did
